    "‡ ‡ While intermediary service providers occasionally choose to subsidize protocol transaction fees § §, application fees are in near all cases paid by the user interacting with the DeFi application.",
    "Because application designers seek to lower the aggregate transaction costs, protocol fees, slippage or impermanent loss through algorithmic financial modelling and incentive alignment, stakeholders must carefully observe the state of the blockchain network.",
    "If a period of network congestion coincides with a period of volatility, the application design may suddenly impose excessive fees or penalties on otherwise standard actions such as withdrawing or adding funds to a lending market [20].",
